10:Tb9fc2,<p><mjx-container class="MathJax" jax="CHTML" style="font-size: 121%;" display="true"><mjx-math display="true" style="margin-left: 0; margin-right: 0;" class=" MJX-TEX"></mjx-math></mjx-container></p>
<p>A convolutional layer is a <a href="Layer%20Types">layer</a> that unlike <a href="Dense%20Layer">dense layers</a> operates on a small section of its inputs at a time. It does this through <a href="Convolution">convolving</a> the <a href="Kernel">kernel</a> over the top of its inputs, this is where it gets its name of the convolutional layer.</p>

<h2>Stride</h2>
<p>The stride controls how the offset of the <a href="Kernel">kernel</a> changes after each <a href="Convolution">convolution</a> iteration.</p>
